OL,3,CCleverly vows to hold perpetrators to
OL,4,Caccount by updating law on spiking
OL,6,FThe has vowed to crack down on spiking
OL,7,Fas he said perpetrators will be "held
OL,8,Fto account" by changes in the law.
OL,10,FJames Cleverly said the government is
OL,11,Fupdating legislation to make it clear
OL,12,Fthat spiking is a crime, as he visited
OL,13,Fofficers during the first national
OL,14,Fweek of action against spiking.
OL,16,FSpiking Intensification Week, which
OL,17,Fruns from March 18 to 24, aims to
OL,18,Fboost police investigations of the
OL,19,Fcrime such as early reporting and
OL,20,Fpolice forensic testing.
