OL,3,CCleverly vows to hold perpetrators to
OL,4,Caccount by updating law on spiking
OL,6,FSpiking is already illegal and happens
OL,7,Fwhen someone puts alcohol or drugs
OL,8,Finto another person's drink or body
OL,9,Fwithout their knowledge or consent.
OL,11,FAccording to the National Police
OL,12,FChiefs' Council (NPCC), forces receive
OL,13,F561 reports of spiking per month but
OL,14,Fit is believed to be underreported
OL,15,Fbecause of harmful "myths and
OL,16,Fstereotypes" against victims.
OL,18,FMr Cleverly told reporters: "The sad
OL,19,Ftruth is we know this is a crime that
OL,20,Fhas been habitually underreported, but
OL,21,Fwe know it is very prevalent.
