OL,3,CCleverly vows to hold perpetrators to
OL,4,Caccount by updating law on spiking
OL,6,F"And of course, what we're doing is
OL,7,Fwe're updating the legislation to make
OL,8,Fit clear and unambiguous that spiking
OL,9,Fis a crime. We prioritise the
OL,10,Fprevention of crimes against women and
OL,11,Fgirls, and the people who perpetrate
OL,12,Fspiking will be held to account."
OL,14,FThe NPCC said all forces in England
OL,15,Fand Wales have taken part in the week
OL,16,Fof action, with some forces including
OL,17,FLeicestershire Police, Humberside
OL,18,FPolice and West Mercia Police
OL,19,Freceiving a further cash boost for
OL,20,Faction such as increased street
OL,21,Fpatrols.
